abstract: Two dozen centrist senators from both parties banded together to push their leaders to a deal to reopen the government. Now comes the hard part.
snippet: Two dozen centrist senators from both parties banded together to push their leaders to a deal to reopen the government. Now comes the hard part.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON â€” The ground rules were simple: Senators wishing to voice their opinion needed to wait their turn and could speak only once they had grabbed hold of a Masai tribal talking stick.

headline_main: With Talking Stick in Hand, Moderate Senators Broke the Shutdown
headline_print_headline: Moderates Broke Impasse on a Promise to Address Immigration

abstract: Liberal and immigration activists said Democrats betrayed young undocumented immigrants by reopening the government after only three days of a shutdown.
snippet: Liberal and immigration activists said Democrats betrayed young undocumented immigrants by reopening the government after only three days of a shutdown.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON â€” The decision by Senate Democrats to end the government shutdown on Monday in exchange for a promised immigration vote enraged liberals, who accused the lawmakers of betrayal and threatened to mount primaries against some of the Democrats who voted yes.

abstract: A group of bipartisan lawmakers emerged as the negotiators behind a potential deal to end the gridlock and reopen the government.
snippet: A group of bipartisan lawmakers emerged as the negotiators behind a potential deal to end the gridlock and reopen the government.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON â€” On the second day of the shutdown, a bipartisan group of senators emerged as a primary force behind the effort to end the gridlock and reopen the government. More than 20 lawmakers, some facing challenging re-election bids, met behind closed doors and brokered a compromise that the Senate advanced 81 to 18 on Monday.

abstract: If the argument seems to amount to a distinction without a difference, neither the White House nor its allies have acknowledged it.
snippet: If the argument seems to amount to a distinction without a difference, neither the White House nor its allies have acknowledged it.
lead_paragraph: Over a three-day weekend at his private club in Palm Beach, Fla., President Trump showed little or no concern about the angry reaction set off by his use of obscenities to describe the third world countries he fears immigrants could come from under a new immigration bill. His base loved what he said, he told guests at the club, Mar-a-Lago, a refrain he repeated in phone calls over the holiday weekend.

abstract: The legislation, which closely hews to a federal bill, would require internet companies to reveal who is paying and to show where content comes from.
snippet: The legislation, which closely hews to a federal bill, would require internet companies to reveal who is paying and to show where content comes from.
lead_paragraph: ALBANY â€” Following a federal push for more disclosure, and amid investigations into Russian meddling into American elections, Gov. Andrew M. Cuomo is proposing legislation to close legal loopholes in New York regarding political ads on the internet, with the goal of pressuring companies like Facebook to root out foreign-based interlopers in online campaigns.
